Metro hits year high on takeover talk . Retailer Metro Holdings touched a year high of S $ 6 . 20 in intraday trade on Friday before sliding to S $ 6 . 10 , up 1 . 60 , or 35 . 56 percent , at 0811 GMT . Its turnover jumped up 5 . 18 million shares . Dealers said speculation had been growing that Metro was a takeover target by First Capital Corp , which already owns a 5 . 6 percent stake in Metro Holdings . The speculated takeover price was S $ 7 . 00 against Metro ' s estimated net asset value of $ 8 . 00 per share , the dealers said . " The punters could be pushing the price up . If the rumour is true , the gains are definitely attractive , " said a broker . 
